{"title_page": "Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu", "text_new": "{{for|the village that bore his name in the 1930s and '40s|Jurilovca}}\n{{short description|Romanian politician}} \n{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n[[Image:VintilaBratianuPrimarulCapitalei-1907-1910.jpg|thumb|Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu]]\n'''Vintil\u0103 Ion Constantin Br\u0103tianu''' (16 September 1867 \u2013 22 December 1930) was a Romanian politician who served as Prime Minister of [[Romania]] between 24 November 1927 and 9 November 1928.\n\nVintil\u0103 and his brothers [[Ionel Br\u0103tianu|Ionel]] and [[Dinu Br\u0103tianu|Dinu]] were the leaders of the [[National Liberal Party (Romania, 1875)|National Liberal Party of Romania]] (founded by their father, [[Ion C. Br\u0103tianu]]). Born at his family's estate of ''Florica'', in [[\u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti, Arge\u0219|\u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti]], [[Arge\u0219 County]], he studied in [[France]] and after returning to Romania entered politics.\n\nHe was an adviser on economic affairs to the Liberal government led by his brother, Ion. During [[World War I]], he was Minister for Munitions and after the war, he served as Finance Minister (1922-1926).\n\nAfter his brother Ion died, he assumed the post of Prime Ministerof Romania until he was forced to resign in 1928 to allow the new [[National Peasants' Party|PN\u0162]] (National Peasants' Party) government of [[Iuliu Maniu]] to take office. He died in [[R\u00e2mnicu V\u00e2lcea]].\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" class=\"center\">\nFile:Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu voluntar, 1885.JPG\nFile:1887 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu la v\u00e2rsta de dou\u0103zeci de ani.PNG\nFile:1910 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu - primarul Bucure\u015ftilor.PNG\nFile:1910 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu Portret.PNG\nFile:1858 - Ion C Br\u0103tianu).PNG\nFile:Vintila Bratianu - Foto01.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== See also == \n* [[Br\u0103tianu family]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://rulers.org/indexb5.html Rulers.org]\n\n{{RomanianPrimeMinisters}}\n{{PNLHeads}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bratianu, Vintila}}\n[[Category:1867 births]]\n[[Category:1930 deaths]]\n[[Category:Br\u0103tianu family|Vintila Bratianu]]\n[[Category:People from \u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti, Arge\u0219]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Romania)]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Defence]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Finance]]\n[[Category:Chairpersons of the National Liberal Party (Romania)]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Bucharest]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Romania]]\n[[Category:Children of national leaders]]\n\n\n{{Romania-mayor-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Romanian politician}} \n{{Unreferenced|date=December 2009}}\n{{for|the village that bore his name in the 1930s and '40s|Jurilovca}}\n[[Image:VintilaBratianuPrimarulCapitalei-1907-1910.jpg|thumb|Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu]]\n'''Vintil\u0103 Ion Constantin Br\u0103tianu''' (16 September 1867 \u2013 22 December 1930) was a Romanian politician who served as Prime Minister of [[Romania]] between 24 November 1927 and 9 November 1928.\n\nVintil\u0103 and his brothers [[Ionel Br\u0103tianu|Ionel]] and [[Dinu Br\u0103tianu|Dinu]] were the leaders of the [[National Liberal Party (Romania, 1875)|National Liberal Party of Romania]] (founded by their father, [[Ion C. Br\u0103tianu]]). Born at his family's estate of ''Florica'', in [[\u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti, Arge\u0219|\u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti]], [[Arge\u0219 County]], he studied in [[France]] and after returning to Romania entered politics.\n\nHe was an adviser on economic affairs to the Liberal government led by his brother, Ion. During [[World War I]], he was Minister for Munitions and after the war, he served as Finance Minister (1922-1926).\n\nAfter his brother Ion died, he assumed the post of Prime Ministerof Romania until he was forced to resign in 1928 to allow the new [[National Peasants' Party|PN\u0162]] (National Peasants' Party) government of [[Iuliu Maniu]] to take office. He died in [[R\u00e2mnicu V\u00e2lcea]].   \n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\" class=\"center\">\nFile:Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu voluntar, 1885.JPG\nFile:1887 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu la v\u00e2rsta de dou\u0103zeci de ani.PNG\nFile:1910 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu - primarul Bucure\u015ftilor.PNG\nFile:1910 - Vintil\u0103 Br\u0103tianu Portret.PNG\nFile:1858 - Ion C Br\u0103tianu).PNG\nFile:Vintila Bratianu - Foto01.jpg\n</gallery>\n\n== See also == \n* [[Br\u0103tianu family]]\n\n==External links==\n*[http://rulers.org/indexb5.html Rulers.org]\n\n{{RomanianPrimeMinisters}}\n{{PNLHeads}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bratianu, Vintila}}\n[[Category:1867 births]]\n[[Category:1930 deaths]]\n[[Category:Br\u0103tianu family|Vintila Bratianu]]\n[[Category:People from \u0218tef\u0103ne\u0219ti, Arge\u0219]]\n[[Category:Members of the Chamber of Deputies (Romania)]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Defence]]\n[[Category:Romanian Ministers of Finance]]\n[[Category:Chairpersons of the National Liberal Party (Romania)]]\n[[Category:Mayors of Bucharest]]\n[[Category:Prime Ministers of Romania]]\n[[Category:Children of national leaders]]\n\n{{Romania-mayor-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Joeykai", "label": "safe", "comment": "clean up", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vintil%C4%83_Br%C4%83tianu"}
