or       = \n|birth_name      =  \n|birth_date      = {{birth date and age|1950|7|30|df=y}}<ref name=interior/>\n|birth_place     = [[Salerno]], [[Campania]], [[Italy]]<ref name=interior/><ref name=sindaco>{{Cite web|url=http://www.comune.salerno.it/allegati/23877.pdf|title=Vincenzo Napoli|work=Comune di Salerno|access-date=15  March 2019}}</ref>\n|death_date      = \n|death_place     = \n|party           = [[Italian Socialist Party]] (1980-1994)<br/>[[Democratic Party of the Left]] (1994-1998)<br/>[[Democrats of the Left]] (1998-2007)<br/>[[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] (since 2007)<ref name=interior/>\n|otherparty      = \n|spouse          = \n|children        = \n|alma_mater      = [[University of Naples Federico II]]<ref name=sindaco/>\n|profession      = architect<ref name=interior/><ref name=sindaco/>\n}}\n'''Vincenzo Napoli''' (born 30 July 1950 in [[Salerno]]) is an Italian politician.<ref name=interior/><ref name=sindaco/>\n\nHe is a member of the [[Democratic Party (Italy)|Democratic Party]] and he was elected [[List of mayors of Salerno|Mayor of Salerno]] on 5 June 2016 and took his office on 14 June.<ref name=interior/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rainews.it/dl/rainews/articoli/Amministrative-Salerno-Eletti-al-primo-turno-940b788c-43d9-48f2-b1cf-d74b5fd5fefa.html|title=Amministrative: a Salerno effetto De Luca, Enzo Napoli oltre il 70%|work=[[Rai News]]|date=6 June 2016|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ilfattoquotidiano.it/2016/06/06/comunali-salerno-2016-stravince-enzo-napoli-candidato-di-de-luca-in-attesa-di-passare-leredita-al-figlio-roberto/2802528/|title=Comunali Salerno 2016, stravince Enzo Napoli, candidato di De Luca. In attesa di passare l'eredit\u00e0 al figlio Roberto|work=[[Il Fatto Quotidiano]]|date=6 June 2016|access-date=24 March 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n==See also==\n*[[2016 Italian local elections]]\n*[[List of mayors of Salerno]]\n\n==External links==\n* {{Cite w